am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: balance theory</span><hr size=1> I think the last time I got hit in a group was when AOE'ing beetles in DN.<br>
<br>
If you're in a &quot;normal&quot; group of Tanks, Cleric, Enc and are getting hit you're not managing aggro correctly.  Grind groups don't need a Wizard who becomes the center of the mob's attention every round.  That is not the Wizard's job IMO unless you need to drag a mob off your Cleric or ENC long enough for a Mez.  Nine times out of ten a root will work to save your Cleric or Chanter and keep you out of trouble as well.  Announce to the group that %T is ROOTED and let the Chanter or Cleric back up out of range to do their jobs.  The tanks will thank you for not pingponging, and the healers and mezzers will realize you're a valuable addtion to the group beyond simply nuking and evacing.<br>
<br>
Zatty Izmee<br>
57 Evacer .. err Evoker<br>
Tunare<br>
Phoenix Alliance<br>
